Stay until the end, its so calming & I find it satisfying.🙏
.
Mediation comes in many forms for the senses. 

𝗪𝗵𝗶𝗰𝗵 𝘀𝘁𝘆𝗹𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝗺𝗲𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝘀𝘂𝗶𝘁𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗺𝗼𝘀𝘁? 👇
.
📽by @yukikawae 🌱
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
Meditation is anything where you are able to be present with one thing and there are many different ways you can get a sense of meditation.
.
Regularly connecting with something that brings you into the present moment is a sign to your mind & body that you are safe & not in need of the stress response, anxiety.
.
Where as regularly connecting to things that cause stress, like fearful news, or constant distractions & info are signs of overwhelm.
.
Meditation
Here are some things that I connect with.

📚Reading takes me to a place in my mind I love the imagination 
🏖The beach sounds & visuals distract all other thoughts I am at peace
🕊Looking for and listening to nature connects me to life, I feel part of it.
🎵Music touches my heart strings, it can lift me high, can help me to connect to emotions inside to release them. I feel alive.
🌞Being in the sun and I start to drink it in, taking deep breaths. I feel energised.
⛈Thunder & rain connects me to our planet. I could listen for ages & wonder at the sights sounds.
.
There are many more visual, sounds, senses that give me that one focus and calms all others.
.
I saw this visual meditation video & thought you guys might enjoy.
.
𝗗𝗶𝗱 𝗶𝘁 𝗯𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗰𝗮𝗹𝗺? 
.
For me I could watch this over & over i get calm from it. & it makes me want to try these actions, I think it would inspire calm.
.
Enjoy 🙏
.
#anxiety #meditation #different #for #everyone #joy #peace #calm #try

Boost wellbeing & immunity.
Win Win Win!

.

.

.

👍Join us on Monday the 19th of october. Both myself & Priyanka @almaformula have collaborated to bring you this challenge & we will both be taking part.
.
🤔We will be consciously working on what we are in control of : behaviours such as 
.
Daily habits
Food choices
Thought Management
Morning rituals
Reconnecting to nature
etc.

All these will impact our thoughts & feelings.
Reduce fear
Reduce anxiety
Boost wellbeing & immunity.
Win Win Win!
.
👉Each Saturday we will go live for a Q & A. After the live, we will be posting up what you need, to be prepared for the week. (things you may already have or are very affordable to get) So that you don't arrive at one day and think "I am not ready" & then decide you can't join in. 
.
👉Each evening between 9pm French time we will be posting up what to do for the following day.
So that you know what to expect, as some of the activities are designed to be, as you wake up.
.
👉You can follow myself & @almaformula we will be doing the challenge ourselves & documenting this in our stories to give you two different perspectives from the challenge as well as your own. 
.
👉There will be links given as we go, for ideas, downloadables etc. as part of the challenge. 
.
👉If you are thinking you can't do this, it may be too long?
.
👉HERE'S a Helpful perception
Life sometimes happens, even myself, I may have a day when it's not possible to achieve that days activity, like too many urgent things may take over. That's fine & not a reason to beat myself up or decide I've failed, feel bad & the choose to not take part the next day. No i'll take the day I need & will be ready the next day.
.
👉Also this is a challenge to be taken with interest & discovery of self. To become aware of what behaviours we choose that may influence our thoughts & feelings. Not to tell ourselves off, but to know where we can make the first step.
.
👉We are in control of our behaviours & this will impact/influence on our though & feelings.
.
👉Up next is the shopping list.
👉Sunday 9pm gmt +1 Monday's challenge Will be posted.
👉Monday websites & links to what you need.
👉Everything will be saved in the highlights & IGTV for you to try at any time.
.
😊

look for the good.

I saw this and thought we all needed a reminder to check up on others, to try not to judge that a behaviour was something bad.👇
.
Chadwick Boseman 1976-2020 : actor : played the black panther ❤ sadly passed away last year after a battle with cancer.
 📽@ stan hiddle tik tok
.
Example, if you didn't know that he was battling cancer what might you assume from his behaviour?
.
He's lazy 
Must have gone out last night 
He's not serious about this commitment 
Etc 
And you'd be wrong.
.
Then with this negative perception that is not true, what would you feel? Angry?
🤬Here i am trying hard & he doesn't care!
Then what might you do?
Ignore him? Be funny, off with him?
Etc 
What would be the consequences?
.
Take this reminder today & try not to judge others, because you don't know anything, so first try compassion, we are all human you'll need that compassion 1 day too.
.
Give anger you'll get defense back 
Give compassion you'll get a human ❤
_______________
.
I am sad that he passed away. His character in the film Black panther was something we had needed for years & was looking forward to seeing more.
.
Watch the film because you could have a negative perception of black people that had been fed to you, & if you do, this will effect how you think, feel & act. How would that effect your behaviour? What would be the consequences?
.
Imagine if someone had already a negative perception of you, how might you react to that? 

Negative? 
Angry?
Defensive?
.
Then what would that cause? 
.
Always in whatever situation you are in check your perspective. Is it true? Question it.
Break the circle. 
.

#blackpanther
#amazingfilm
#longoverdue
#truth
#perceptions
#celebrate 
#chadwickboseman
#compassion
#love #community

node.text:
If you feel you've fallen into an 𝗮𝗻𝘅𝗶𝗲𝘁𝘆 hole and you don't know how to get out it's not your fault, its normal that you don't know how to get out if you've never been in one before & never learnt about anxiety, never gotten out of it. Read 👇
.
🎨@wholesomecomic
✒@anxiety_wellbeing
.
Quote 🗣
This guy's walking down the street when he falls in a hole. The walls are so steep he can't get out.
"A doctor passes by and the guy shouts up, 'Hey you. Can you help me out?' The doctor writes a prescription, throws it down in the hole and moves on.
"Then a priest comes along and the guy shouts up, 'Father, I'm down in this hole can you help me out?' The priest writes out a prayer, throws it down in the hole and moves on
"Then a friend walks by, 'Hey, Joe, it's me can you help me out?' And the friend jumps in the hole. Our guy says, 'Are you stupid? Now we're both down here.' The friend says, 'Yeah, but I've been down here before and I know the way out.
-from the west wing with hat tip to Peter Shankman.
.
.
Someone who doesn't know is not silly or stupid. They are someone who needs to be shown, to ask questions, some guidance, to see it, to practice it  that's how you learn. That's how you know ❤
.
Please take these words with comfort, you can feel better, you're in need of finding out how to get out.
.
So if you find yourself shocked that you are feeling very anxious and then telling yourself you shouldn't be feeling anxious, or believing that you're stuck. speak to yourself. I may feel stuck, I am not broken I am in need of learning & in need of a hand. 
.
This page is dedicated to helping you get out of an anxiety circle.
.
I was in that place 20 years ago & I know how to get out.
.
If holistic/cbt coaching is something you would want to try contact me for more info on anxiety.wellbeing.coach@gmail.com or go to the link in the bio for coaching information 
.
5 week sessions: 6 available places per 5 week blocks. There are 2 spaces left starting the 11th of October & open for November. 
.
Take care.
.

node.text:
If you 𝗯𝗲𝗹𝗶𝗲𝘃𝗲 it's never enough, you'll be exhausted & upset chasing enough that never comes, not knowing that👇

🎨@catscafecomics 
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
It was never not enough, you just think it is.
.
Why might you think that?
.
Take yourself back, when was maybe the first time you thought to yourself💭I'm not enough💭What I did was not enough💭I must do this that & the other to ensure people might like me.
.
Somewhere back there in that situation you were in you perceived it all to be about you.

Examples
.
😔They call me names, I'm not pretty enought, good enough etc.

👉Without the knowledge that, kids are immature & say anything because usually they may be, being shut down at 🏠 or have issues communicating, or envious etc. This comes out as 'you are_____.'etc There are reasons but its not you, its them.
.
😔Doesn't matter what I do at 🏠 they're not happy, good grades are not good enough, if I do do good they say OK 'next' thing to achieve. Its never enough.
.
Without knowing that in some 🏠's, you are enough already, or that for mum & dad its thier ideas of success & they have fear that if you don't achieve always it may say something about them or you may be judged etc They prob do not realise what doing that really means & that you are already enough you need to hear it, from them or from you. Its not about you they have fears.
.
😔Someone in my family drinks & is sad, angry,  abusive, distant etc. Why don't they choose me instead of drink? I am not enough to give it up.
.
Without realising that they are not not choosing you, they are struggling to cope with something they have no skills over, are stuck in a circle, this is a coping mechanism they had at a time of stuggle & is now a habit & prob all the reasons they tried to cope are still in their head. Doesnt mean its ok for you to go through that but means, You were & are enough. Its about them. 
.
So if you did perceive something to be about with the only knowledge you had at the time it would make sense to beleive that your🌎 depends on you insuring you are enough.
.
❤ Now you have another perception🤔 it was never about you, you were & are enough, you can try to be happy just being you

node.text:
Who taught you to put others first? 𝗪𝗵𝘆 do we do that? How can we change?
.
🎨@theopeninvite 
✒@anxiety_wellbeing
.
Everything we think & do is taught to us by others or how we perveived things
.
Seeing someone do it that way
Hearing someone telling you to do it that way or
The way you pecrieved a situation to be, influencing your idea of what you do.
.
Ex's
If you saw your parents putting others first, job, partners before themselves & thEY believed that to be the right thing to do. You learnt thats how to be in your🌎

If you heard them say, 'be good, don't cry, I am tired'. (but you need to cry)
Or 'Eat that'(but you're not hungry) you can't leave until its finished'. You are learning that your survival is wrapped around making them happy above your needs. 
.
If mum is distant because she is going through a stressful situation, & doesn't want to pass that to you. But you see this as rejection, you may start to try to please her believing that the distance is because there is something wrong with you.
.
Survive?
As youngsters we need these people, they're our care givers, we need them to survive. They are showing you how to survive with them, teaching habits, behaviours, ideas of thinking etc
.
⚠️
Im not putting these people down, they are human like us, trying to do what they believe to be right, doing things that they were taught also but that also doesn't mean that it is right, because, if nowyou put others always before you, you will be at risk of neglecting your human needs feeling ill, anxious, low etc.
.
How can we try not to?
Its good to be aware of why we do that ⬆️
To understand that it is human⬆️
To know it is taught⬆️
Or that it comes from our interpretation of an event when we didn't have all the info⬆️ 
.
That means we can learn other ways, we can work on other perceptions ,look at other possible meanings.
.
⬇️ 
If you notice you have just put yourself last but you are in need, its ok you're normal but, you need to practice saying, no🗣I need to look after myself, next time maybe. Its never doing it before that feels strange but once or twice you will start to get the hang of it.
.
Stay empathetic we need U but look after you2
.
#anxiety

node.text:
Mornings can 𝗳𝗲𝗲𝗹 like 'on your marks, get set, go'.🏃‍♂ But could it be more like, 'What can I enjoy about this beautiful day? Whilst I get to do some other things too👇
.
🎨@iuliastration 🌙
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
It depends on how we speak to ourselves in the morning.
.
If you wake up & think💭
🗣What do I need to do?🤔
🗣How am I going to do it?😑
🗣I am i even happy?😔
🗣I need to eat too?🙄
🗣Oh there's lots to do!😵
🗣Its gonna be a long day!🥴
🗣All i wanna do is go back to bed😴
🗣Or just not do this stuff.🙈
.
All this before you are out of bed!
.
Woooooow, its gonna be a tough day. This thinking, believed, not questioned, continued, feared means the day is horrible, one long job, a dreaded event, something to avoid. Anxious. & how does the next day feel?
.
Ps You are normal if you do think this, we get taught to view this life as👇
School!
Work!
Earn!
Pay!
Even your funeral they want you to think about paying for now. I mean really???
.
Good news is you do not have to follow this way.
.
Lets say that today or tomorrow you wake up & even if you notice these thoughts you say.
OK normal, I've been taught this but I am going to say instead.
.
🗣I only want to get up, breathe, stretch, open & look out of the window, see the weather, listen, look for nature, say hello to it.🥰 
.
🗣After my time to wake up & get ready I will write down a manageable list of things I would like to accomplish today. Even better I may do this the night before.👍
 
🗣I am not focused on my emotions, let them flow, its not my job to ensure happiness. I am safe, I am enough, I am learning, I am human.❤
.
🗣I hope this day feels longer, I'll never get this day back, I must celebrate my day. Thank you universe❤
.
🗣I want to enjoy this day, how can I make pockets of joy today? My favorite songs? Etc
.
🗣I don't have to, I get to, & I will enjoy my day. 
.
Practice this daily
If you work on learning a new meaning of life, you'll influence your thoughts, that will influence your feelings & behaviours.
.
Time to enjoy this wonderful day, with work on the side ❤❤
.
#anxiety #school #learntobeaworker #work #life #important #survive include #joy #love #day #night #amazing #gift

Meditation is anything where you are able to be present with one thing and there are many different ways you can get a sense of meditation.
.
Regularly connecting with something that brings you into the present moment is a sign to your mind & body that you are safe & not in need of the stress response, anxiety.
.
Where as regularly connecting to things that cause stress, like fearful news, or constant distractions & info are signs of overwhelm.
.
Meditation
Here are some things that I connect with.

📚Reading takes me to a place in my mind I love the imagination 
🏖The beach sounds & visuals distract all other thoughts I am at peace
🕊Looking for and listening to nature connects me to life, I feel part of it.
🎵Music touches my heart strings, it can lift me high, can help me to connect to emotions inside to release them. I feel alive.
🌞Being in the sun and I start to drink it in, taking deep breaths. I feel energised.
⛈Thunder & rain connects me to our planet. I could listen for ages & wonder at the sights sounds.

node.text:
𝗧𝗶𝗿𝗲𝗱 of trying to make lemonade? Maybe we could ignore some of the 🍋's?
.
🎨@will_santino_illustration
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
🍋IGNORE THE lemons? What do you mean?
.
Let me take you back 20+ years ago. 
I had a panic response on an underground train that after, although shook up I didn't have any long term issues. Then I had another one in a shopping mall, ran to the bus, ran home & from there i was panicking every 30 minutes for 6 months.
Everything was scary! Caused more panic.
There was not 1 second in the day of calm.
I felt like I was in a storm of lemons, couldn't see my was out. Gradually feeling like there were tons of them on me!
.
To cut a long story short, I became afraid of what i would do if nothing changed. I saw a doc, a cbt therapist, learnt about anxiety, what was happening, why I was responding, went back to school learnt about the brain, nutrition, psychology etc for more info on the causes.
20+ years later I am a cbt practitioner, holistic anxiety coach. 
.
But what did I learn that was the best piece of info to come out of all that?
.
Not every🍋is true.

I beleived because of that one panic response that everything coming my way after that was a 🍋(fear)& for my full attention. That I was helpless.(I wasn't)This caused more fear & caused more panic, then I was only responding😱
.
Sometimes lemons can be
.
🍋False Evidence Appearing Real
🍋Fearful Outside influence 
.
Example of outside🍋's
Right now the media are throwing these things at us everyday, causing fear, we are trying to survive, but look at the ones in charge are they doing that?
.
Could it be that alot of this info is hearsay, maybes, might's, pressumued, estimated, worst case scenario, feared to be? Etc 
.
In my control👇
.
🍋I was believing I was in constant danger but I wasn't. I had to start saying that although I feel scared I am safe. Although I think something bad might happen, will it? Ask questions get interested instead of scared.
.
A belief, thought, feeling can be untrue.
.
You can
Before you react 
Try not to believe the 1st meaning
Pay attention to the wording
Switch off
Distract
.
Work on you. Outside is only in your influence not your control. 
.
#anxiety

You know what you need 𝗯𝘂𝘁, a doubtful thought takes your attention & then what?
Why do we get this type of thought? What should you do?
.
🎨@silviadoesdrawings
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 

Then what? 
Well you'll already be tired & in need but now you might start to feel down & anxious. Because any fearful thoughts like👇cause anxiety

I need to but👇
💭What if someone judges me 
💭What if they think Im lazy
💭I can't, must not
.
💭So now Im stuck, I have to feel this way or be afraid, which is worse?
.
💭How will I continue my day?
.
💭I'll be like this forever its helpless
.
Then before you know it these thoughts are enough to signal danger & panic.
All this on top of your needs 
.
❤
.
We get these types of thoughts from our past & present experiences.

Did anyone say you were lazy before? Or say something that you thought meant the same thing? 
Did anyone act as thought taking a break was wrong?
Have you percieved things to be, not good at all if you're not constantly showing you are being productive?
How do you view society? Feel like working harder?
 
This is where the influence of your beliefs, ideas, thoughts comes from but is it true? Or do you just think it is because of what you have experienced before?
.
It is normal for your mind to remember past events & equate them to be the meaning for the future. The minds job is to find meaning for everything & protect you.
 
So if you've learnt 
Better not👇
Upset anyone by looking lazy
Because someone will judge me
Take a break they will tell me off 
Better have a reason for relaxing
Etc
.
Then relaxing everyday, & not just when you need it or relaxing at all will feel like a tug of war. Its normal considering all these experiences from the past.
.
The good news is the past doesn't=the future & beliefs, ideas, thoughts change because we can influence the meaning, by influencing our perception.
.
Things to tell yourself
If I need a break I do.
I dont need to justify my meaning.
If today its not possible then this weekend I am cancelling plans because I need it.
I will say I need a break or I will breakdown. #human being over here.
Its not my job to change what my taking a break means to them.
I need it.
.
#anxiety
